                sovereign
            bonds</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">人民幣國債</term>) means any bonds denominated in the
            Renminbi and issued in Hong Kong by the Central People’s Government.</def></section><section id="ID_1438402591406_003" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-08-27" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Exemption from profits tax</heading><subsection id="ID_1438410954796_018" name="1" temporalId="s3_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><leadIn>A person is exempt from the payment of profits tax chargeable under Part IV of the Ordinance in respect of sums received by or accrued to the person as—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438410954796_026" name="a" temporalId="s3_1_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>interest paid or payable on Renminbi sovereign bonds; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438410954796_034" name="b" temporalId="s3_1_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>profits on the sale or other disposal or on the redemption on maturity or presentment of Renminbi sovereign bonds.</content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438410954796_041" name="2" temporalId="s3_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>This section applies in relation to profits tax chargeable for the year of assessment commencing on 1 April 2009 and for all subsequent years of assessment.</content></subsection></section></main></subLeg>